21 PART XIII. CODIFY THE ESSENTIAL HOLDINGS OF ROE V. WADE AND
22 PLANNED PARENTHOOD OF SOUTHEASTERN PA V. CASEY
23 SECTION 13.1.(a) Chapter 90 of the General Statutes is amended by adding a new
24 Article to read:
25 "Article 1P.
26 "Codify Roe and Casey Protections.
27 "§ 90-21.170. Short title.
28 This Article shall be known and may be cited as "Codify Roe and Casey Protections."
29 "§ 90-21.171. Purpose.
30 The purpose of this Article is to codify the essential holdings of Roe v. Wade, 410 U.S. 113
31 (1973), and Planned Parenthood of Southeastern Pennsylvania v. Casey, 505 U.S. 833 (1992).
32 "§ 90-21.172. Allowable requirements.
33 (a) The State shall not impose an undue burden on the ability of a woman to choose
34 whether or not to terminate a pregnancy before fetal viability.
35 (b) The State may do any of the following:
36 (1) Restrict the ability of a woman to choose whether or not to terminate a
37 pregnancy after fetal viability, unless such a termination is necessary to
38 preserve the life or health of the woman.
39 (2) Enact laws, rules, or regulations, as applicable, to further the health or safety
40 of a woman seeking to terminate a pregnancy.
41 (c) For the purposes of this section, the term "undue burden" means any burden that
42 places a substantial obstacle in the path of a woman seeking to terminate a pregnancy prior to
43 fetal viability.
44 (d) Nothing in this Article shall be construed to have any effect on laws regarding
45 conscience protection."
46 SECTION 13.1.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law.
